com.ibm.async_util.locks

Class FairAsyncReadWriteLock

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.async_util.locks.FairAsyncReadWriteLock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AsyncReadWriteLock
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FairAsyncStampedLock

    public class FairAsyncReadWriteLock
extends Object
implements AsyncReadWriteLock
    An implementation of the AsyncReadWriteLock interface which enforces reader/writer fairness -- i.e. new readers will queue behind waiting writers

    • Method Detail

      • acquireReadLock

        public final CompletionStage<AsyncReadWriteLock.ReadLockToken> acquireReadLock()
        Description copied from interface: AsyncReadWriteLock
        Acquire this read-lock. If the associated write-lock has not been acquired, the returned future will be immediately complete. Otherwise, the returned future will complete when the lock is no longer exclusively acquired by a writer.

        The AsyncReadWriteLock.ReadLockToken held by the returned future is used to release the read lock after it has been acquired and the read-lock-protected action has completed.

        Specified by:
        acquireReadLock in interface AsyncReadWriteLock

      • tryReadLock

        public final Optional<AsyncReadWriteLock.ReadLockToken> tryReadLock()
        Attempt to immediately acquire the read lock, returning a populated Optional if the lock is not currently held by a writer and there are no writers queued in waiting (i.e. this acquire is "fair" and will not barge ahead of waiting writers).
        Specified by:
        tryReadLock in interface AsyncReadWriteLock
        Returns:
        An Optional holding a AsyncReadWriteLock.ReadLockToken if the lock is not held by a writer; otherwise an empty Optional

      • acquireWriteLock

        public final CompletionStage<AsyncReadWriteLock.WriteLockToken> acquireWriteLock()
        Description copied from interface: AsyncReadWriteLock
        Exclusively acquire this write-lock. If another associated write-lock or read-lock has not been acquired, the returned future will be immediately complete. Otherwise, the returned future will complete when the lock is no longer held by any readers or an exclusive writer.

        The AsyncReadWriteLock.WriteLockToken held by the returned future is used to release the write lock after it has been acquired and the write-lock-protected action has completed.

        Specified by:
        acquireWriteLock in interface AsyncReadWriteLock

      • tryWriteLock

        public final Optional<AsyncReadWriteLock.WriteLockToken> tryWriteLock()

        Attempt to immediately acquire the write lock, returning a populated Optional if the lock is not currently held by a writer or any readers.
        Specified by:

        Returns:
        An Optional holding a AsyncReadWriteLock.WriteLockToken if the lock is not held by a writer or any readers; otherwise an empty Optional
